Notes
	•	Thread‑safety: the sender is a lazy, double‑checked singleton; safe across invocations.
	•	Error handling: send() logs and throws so the Functions runtime will retry; you can also hook your existing ErrorWriter in the catch if you want to persist the failed payload.
	•	Schema stability: versioned via schemaVersion. If you add fields later, bump to "1.1" and keep old fields for backward compatibility.
	•	Small messages: the changes list carries only the tracked deltas you already computed.

